def Comb(n,k):
    return factorial(n) / (factorial(k) * factorial(n-k))

def dag(n):
    result = 0
    if n==0:
        return 1
    else:
        for k in range(1,n+1):
            result += (-1)**(k-1) * Comb(n,k)* dag(n-k) * 2**(k*(n-k))
        return int(result)
    
print("The number of possible DAGs is: ", dag(len(df.columns)))

class BayesianNetwork:
    
    def __init__(self, graph, data):
        self.graph = graph
        self.data = data
        self.nodes = data.columns.values
        self.tcp = {k:None for k in self.nodes}
        for k in self.tcp.keys():
            parents = list(self.graph._pred[k].keys())
            if len(parents) == 0:
                self.tcp[k] = self.data[k].value_counts().div(len(self.data)).to_frame().reset_index()
                self.tcp[k].columns = [k,"P"]
            else:
                self.tcp[k] = self.data.groupby(parents)[k].value_counts().unstack().fillna(0)
                self.tcp[k] = self.tcp[k].div(self.tcp[k].sum(axis=1),axis=0)
                self.tcp[k] = self.tcp[k].stack().to_frame().reset_index()
                self.tcp[k].rename(columns={0:"P"},inplace=True)
                
    def request(self,y,x):
        variables = np.array(y+list(x.keys()))
        variables_caches = np.setdiff1d(self.nodes,variables)
        tables = list(self.tcp.values())
        tables_list = []
        for table in tables:
            for v in x.keys():
                if v in table.columns:
                    table = table.loc[table[v] == x[v],:]
            tables_list.append(table)
        tables = tables_list
        for v in variables_caches:
            factors = []
            j = 0
            for i in range(len(tables)):
                if v in tables[j].columns:
                    factors.append(tables.pop(j))
                else:
                    j += 1
            while len(factors) != 1:
                print("length of factors: ",len(factors))
                a = factors.pop()
                b = factors.pop()
                x = a.merge(b,left_on=v,right_on=v)
                x["P"] = x["P_x"] * x["P_y"]
                x.drop(columns=["P_x","P_y"],inplace=True)
                x = x.loc[:,~x.columns.str.endswith("_y")]
                columns_to_rename = [c for c in x.columns if c.endswith("_x")]
                x = x.rename(columns={k:k.replace("_x","") for k in columns_to_rename})
                factors.append(x)
            factors[0] = factors[0].groupby(list(factors[0].columns.values[factors[0].columns.values != v][:-1])).P.sum().to_frame().reset_index()
            tables.append(factors[0])
        while len(tables) != 1:
            for v in variables:
                j=0
                contain_v = []
                for i in range(len(tables)):
                    if v in tables[j].columns:
                        contain_v.append(tables.pop(j))
                    else:
                        j += 1
                while len(contain_v) != 1:
                    a = contain_v.pop()
                    b = contain_v.pop()
                    x = a.merge(b,left_on=v,right_on=v)
                    x["P"] = x["P_x"] * x["P_y"]
                    x.drop(columns=["P_x","P_y"],inplace=True)
                    x = x.loc[:,~x.columns.str.endswith("_y")]
                    columns_to_rename = [c for c in x.columns if c.endswith("_x")]
                    x = x.rename(columns={k:k.replace("_x","") for k in columns_to_rename})
                    contain_v.append(x)
                tables.append(contain_v[0])
        tables[0]["P"] = tables[0]["P"].div(tables[0]["P"].sum())
        return tables[0]
